<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1172098314323">
<term>degree of freedom</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1172096056226">independent kind of motion possessing energy, such as the kinetic energy of motion in one of the three orthogonal spatial directions</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1172098284452">
<term>equipartition theorem</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1172098391682">theorem that the energy of a classical thermodynamic system is shared equally among its degrees of freedom</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>

